==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haloid
<hw>Ha"loid</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"loid ⟦or⟧ h⟦acr⟧l"oid)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"a`ls</grk>, <grk>"alo`s</grk> salt + <ets>-oid</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>halo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Resembling
salt; -- said of certain binary compounds consisting of a metal united
to a negative element or radical, and now chiefly applied to the
chlorides, bromides, iodides, and sometimes also to the fluorides and
cyanides.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A haloid
substance.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
